So disappointing. This was our first time going to this Clyde's. We went for their breakfast with Santa. Santa was very disappointing, even to the kids. He was a young and obviously thin guy with very dark hair with a fake beard and wig slapped on--not like what one expects to see in a decent Santa. It wasn't really a "Breakfast with Santa," but more a breakfast in the same building as Santa. Santa sat in a corner of the restaurant where parents could take the kids to see him.  The flavor of the food was good but the portions were ridiculous. The "Jumbo Crabcake" sandwich we ordered looked like a slider. It would have easily fit on half an English Muffin as part of the eggs Benedict. We should have ordered that for the same price because we would have gotten two crab cakes. Similarly, the quiche was disappointing. It was also a small portion though the flavor was fine.  We rarely saw our server and had to track him down to get the check. I opted to stick with water for my beverage and my glass wasn't filled once during the meal, though he did top off other people's at our table. Very odd.  We won't be returning to this Clyde's whoch is a shame because the decor was nice and it's convenient to the metro. They just don't even seem to try.
